~~~
1   __HEAD
2     efi_signature_nop       
3     b       primary_entry
4     .quad   0    
5     le64sym _kernel_size_le 
6     le64sym _kernel_flags_le  
7     .quad   0   
8     .quad   0             
9     .quad   0             
10    .ascii  ARM64_IMAGE_MAGIC   
11    .long   .Lpe_header_offset  
12    __EFI_PE_HEADER
13  __INIT
~~~


2행 : special NOP to identity as PE/COFF executable, efi-head.S 에 매크로 정의되어 있음.

3행 : branch to kernel start, magic, 실행과정은 head.S에 정의 되어있음.

4행 : Image load offset from start of RAM, little-endian

5행 : Effective size of kernel image, little-endian

6행 : Informative flags, little-endian

7~9행 : reserved

10행 : Magic number

11행 : Offset to the PE header.

12행 : efi-head.S 에 매크로 정의되어 있음.

# 2. primary_entry

~~~
1   SYM_CODE_START(primary_entry)
2     bl      preserve_boot_args
3     bl      init_kernel_el       
4     adrp    x23, __PHYS_OFFSET
5     and     x23, x23, MIN_KIMG_ALIGN - 1
6     bl      set_cpu_boot_mode_flag
7     bl      __create_page_tables

# 2.1 preserve_boot_args


Preserve the arguments passed by the bootloader in x0 .. x3

~~~
1   SYM_CODE_START_LOCAL(preserve_boot_args)
2     mov     x21, x0 
3     adr_l   x0, boot_args 
4     stp     x21, x1, [x0] 
5     stp     x2, x3, [x0, #16]
6     dmb     sy  
7     add     x1, x0, #0x20 
8     b       dcache_inval_poc
9 SYM_CODE_END(preserve_boot_args)
~~~


2행 : x21=FDT

6행 : needed before dc ivac with MMU off

7행 : 4 x 8 bytes

8행 : tail call


# 2.2 init_kernel_el

Starting from EL2 or EL1, configure the CPU to execute at the highest reachable EL supported by the kernel in a chosen default state. If dropping from EL2 to EL1, configure EL2 before configuring EL1. Since we cannot always rely on ERET synchronizing writes to sysregs (e.g. if SCTLR_ELx.EOS is clear), we place an ISB prior to ERET. Returns either BOOT_CPU_MODE_EL1 or BOOT_CPU_MODE_EL2 in w0 if booted in EL1 or EL2 respectively.


~~~
1   SYM_FUNC_START(init_kernel_el)
2     mrs     x0, CurrentEL
3     cmp     x0, #CurrentEL_EL2
4     b.eq    init_el2
5   SYM_INNER_LABEL(init_el1, SYM_L_LOCAL)
6     mov_q   x0, INIT_SCTLR_EL1_MMU_OFF
7     msr     sctlr_el1, x0
8     isb
9     mov_q   x0, INIT_PSTATE_EL1
10    msr     spsr_el1, x0
11    msr     elr_el1, lr
12    mov     w0, #BOOT_CPU_MODE_EL1
13    eret
14  SYM_INNER_LABEL(init_el2, SYM_L_LOCAL)
15    mov_q   x0, HCR_HOST_NVHE_FLAGS
16    msr     hcr_el2, x0
17    isb
18    init_el2_state

19    adr_l   x0, __hyp_stub_vectors
20    msr     vbar_el2, x0
21    isb

22    mrs     x0, hcr_el2
23    and     x0, x0, #HCR_E2H
24    cbz     x0, 1f

25    mov_q   x0, INIT_SCTLR_EL1_MMU_OFF
26    msr_s   SYS_SCTLR_EL12, x0

27    mov     x0, #INIT_PSTATE_EL2
28    msr     spsr_el1, x0
29    adr     x0, __cpu_stick_to_vhe
30    msr     elr_el1, x0
31    eret

1:
32    mov_q   x0, INIT_SCTLR_EL1_MMU_OFF
33    msr     sctlr_el1, x0
34    msr     elr_el2, lr
35    mov     w0, #BOOT_CPU_MODE_EL2
36    eret
37  __cpu_stick_to_vhe:
38    mov     x0, #HVC_VHE_RESTART
39    hvc     #0
40    mov     x0, #BOOT_CPU_MODE_EL2
41    ret
42  SYM_FUNC_END(init_kernel_el)
~~~


19~21행 : Hypervisor stub

22~24행 : Fruity CPUs seem to haveHCR_EL2.E2H set to RES1, making it impossible to start in nVHE mode. Is that compliant with the architecture? Absolutely not!

25~26행 : Switching to VHE requires a sane SCTLR_EL1 as a start

27~31행 : Force an eret into a helper "function", and let it return to our original caller... This makes sure that we have initialised the basic PSTATE state.

# 2.5 set_cpu_boot_mode_flag

Sets the __boot_cpu_mode flag depending on the CPU boot mode passed in w0. See arch/arm64/include/asm/virt.h for more info.

~~~
1   SYM_FUNC_START_LOCAL(set_cpu_boot_mode_flag)
2     adr_l   x1, __boot_cpu_mode
3     cmp     w0, #BOOT_CPU_MODE_EL2
4     b.ne    1f
5     add     x1, x1, #4
6     1:      str     w0, [x1]
7     dmb     sy
8     dc      ivac, x1
9   SYM_FUNC_END(set_cpu_boot_mode_flag)
~~~

6행 : Save CPU boot mode

8행 : Invalidate potentially stale cache line ret



# 2.6 __create_page_tables

Setup the initial page tables. We only setup the barest amount which is required to get the kernel running. The following sections are required: 

- identity mapping to enable the MMU (low address, TTBR0)   
- first few MB of the kernel linear mapping to jump to once the MMU has been enabled


~~~
 1:  SYM_FUNC_START_LOCAL(__create_page_tables)
 2:          mov     x28, lr
 3:          adrp    x0, init_pg_dir
 4:          adrp    x1, init_pg_end
 5:          bl      dcache_inval_poc
 6:          adrp    x0, init_pg_dir
 7:          adrp    x1, init_pg_end
 8:          sub     x1, x1, x0
 9:  1:      stp     xzr, xzr, [x0], #16
10:          stp     xzr, xzr, [x0], #16
11:          stp     xzr, xzr, [x0], #16
12:          stp     xzr, xzr, [x0], #16
13:          subs    x1, x1, #64
14:          b.ne    1b
15:          mov     x7, SWAPPER_MM_MMUFLAGS
16:          adrp    x0, idmap_pg_dir
17:          adrp    x3, __idmap_text_start     
18:  #ifdef CONFIG_ARM64_VA_BITS_52
19:          mrs_s   x6, SYS_ID_AA64MMFR2_EL1
20:          and     x6, x6, #(0xf << ID_AA64MMFR2_LVA_SHIFT)
21:          mov     x5, #52
22:          cbnz    x6, 1f
23:  #endif
24:          mov     x5, #VA_BITS_MIN
25:  1:
26:          adr_l   x6, vabits_actual
27:          str     x5, [x6]
28:          dmb     sy
29:          dc      ivac, x6 
30:  #if (VA_BITS < 48)
31:  #define EXTRA_SHIFT     (PGDIR_SHIFT + PAGE_SHIFT - 3)
32:  #define EXTRA_PTRS      (1 << (PHYS_MASK_SHIFT - EXTRA_SHIFT))
33:  #if VA_BITS != EXTRA_SHIFT
34:  #error "Mismatch between VA_BITS and page size/number of translation levels"
35:  #endif
36:          mov     x4, EXTRA_PTRS
37:          create_table_entry x0, x3, EXTRA_SHIFT, x4, x5, x6
38:  #else
39:          mov     x4, #1 << (PHYS_MASK_SHIFT - PGDIR_SHIFT)
40:          str_l   x4, idmap_ptrs_per_pgd, x5
41:  #endif
42:  1:
43:          ldr_l   x4, idmap_ptrs_per_pgd
44:          adr_l   x6, __idmap_text_end
45:          map_memory x0, x1, x3, x6, x7, x3, x4, x10, x11, x12, x13, x14
46:          adrp    x0, init_pg_dir
47:          mov_q   x5, KIMAGE_VADDR
48:          add     x5, x5, x23
49:          mov     x4, PTRS_PER_PGD
50:          adrp    x6, _end
51:          adrp    x3, _text
52:          sub     x6, x6, x3
53:          add     x6, x6, x5
54:          map_memory x0, x1, x5, x6, x7, x3, x4, x10, x11, x12, x13, x14
55:          dmb     sy
56:          adrp    x0, idmap_pg_dir
57:          adrp    x1, idmap_pg_end
58:          bl      dcache_inval_poc
59:          adrp    x0, init_pg_dir
60:          adrp    x1, init_pg_end
61:          bl      dcache_inval_poc
62:          ret     x28
63:  SYM_FUNC_END(__create_page_tables)
~~~


3~5행 : Invalidate the init page tables to avoid potential dirty cache lines being evicted. Other page tables are allocated in rodata as part of the kernel image, and thus are clean to the PoC per the boot protocol.

6~15행 : Clear the init page tables.

16행 : Create the identity mapping.

17행 : __pa(__idmap_text_start)

29행 : Invalidate potentially stale cache line

33~38행 : If VA_BITS < 48, we have to configure an additional table level. First, we have to verify our assumption that the current value of VA_BITS was chosen such that all translation levels are fully utilised, and that lowering T0SZ will always result in an additional translation level to be configured.

39~45행 : If VA_BITS == 48, we don't have to configure an additional translation level, but the top-level table has more entries.

44행 : __pa(__idmap_text_end)

46~54행 : Map the kernel image (starting with PHYS_OFFSET).

47행 : compile time __va(_text)

48행 :  add KASLR displacement

50행 : runtime __pa(_end)

51행 : runtime __pa(_text)

52행 : _end - _text

53행 : runtime __va(_end)

55~62행 : Since the page tables have been populated with non-cacheable accesses (MMU disabled), invalidate those tables again to remove any speculatively loaded cache lines.

# 2.8.1 __enable_mmu

~~~
 1:  SYM_FUNC_START(__enable_mmu)
 2:          mrs     x2, ID_AA64MMFR0_EL1
 3:          ubfx    x2, x2, #ID_AA64MMFR0_TGRAN_SHIFT, 4
 4:          cmp     x2, #ID_AA64MMFR0_TGRAN_SUPPORTED_MIN
 5:          b.lt    __no_granule_support
 6:          cmp     x2, #ID_AA64MMFR0_TGRAN_SUPPORTED_MAX
 7:          b.gt    __no_granule_support
 8:          update_early_cpu_boot_status 0, x2, x3
 9:          adrp    x2, idmap_pg_dir
10:          phys_to_ttbr x1, x1
11:          phys_to_ttbr x2, x2
12:          msr     ttbr0_el1, x2   
13:          offset_ttbr1 x1, x3
14:          msr     ttbr1_el1, x1
15:          isb
16:          set_sctlr_el1   x0
17:          ret
18:  SYM_FUNC_END(__enable_mmu)
~~~

12행 : load TTBR0

14행 : load TTBR1

# 2.8.2 relocate_kernel 

~~~
 1:  SYM_FUNC_START_LOCAL(__relocate_kernel)
 2:          ldr     w9, =__rela_offset
 3:          ldr     w10, =__rela_size
 4:          mov_q   x11, KIMAGE_VADDR
 5:          add     x11, x11, x23
 6:          add     x9, x9, x11
 7:          add     x10, x9, x10
 8:  0:      cmp     x9, x10
 9:          b.hs    1f
10:          ldp     x12, x13, [x9], #24
11:          ldr     x14, [x9, #-8]
12:          cmp     w13, #R_AARCH64_RELATIVE
13:          b.ne    0b
14:          add     x14, x14, x23
15:          str     x14, [x12, x23]
16:          b       0b
17:  #ifdef CONFIG_RELR
18:  1:
19:          ldr     w9, =__relr_offset
20:          ldr     w10, =__relr_size
21:          add     x9, x9, x11
22:          add     x10, x9, x10
23:          sub     x15, x23, x24
24:          cbz     x15, 7f
25:          mov     x24, x23 
26:  2:      cmp     x9, x10
27:          b.hs    7f
28:          ldr     x11, [x9], #8
29:          tbnz    x11, #0, 3f
30:          add     x13, x11, x23
31:          ldr     x12, [x13]
32:          add     x12, x12, x15
33:          str     x12, [x13], #8
34:          b       2b
35:  3:      mov     x14, x13
36:  4:      lsr     x11, x11, #1
37:          cbz     x11, 6f
38:          tbz     x11, #0, 5f
39:          ldr     x12, [x14]
40:          add     x12, x12, x15
41:          str     x12, [x14]
42:  5:      add     x14, x14, #8
43:          b       4b
44:  6:      add     x13, x13, #(8 * 63)
45:          b       2b
46:  7:
47:  #endif
48:          ret
49:  SYM_FUNC_END(__relocate_kernel)
~~~

# 2.8.3 __primary_switched
